    "Narration:"
    "You let the pendant rest against your sternum and stand with the night at your back. There is no triumphant banner to raise. There is only the slow, hard work of staying and the humility of admitting that some harms wore the face of help."
    "You breathe once, deeply, and the salt air fills your lungs — bracing, bitter, honest. You close the notebook, tuck it against your ribs as if it were the only armor left that fits, and walk"
    "back toward the lab where the kits still wait to be used, and sometimes misused."

